{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:proverbs.22",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 22,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 22 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:1",
      "text": "A good name is better than great riches: and good favour is above silver and gold.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:2",
      "text": "The rich and poor have met one another: the Lord is the maker of them both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:3",
      "text": "The prudent man saw the evil, and hid himself: the simple passed on, and suffered loss.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:4",
      "text": "The fruit of humility is the fear of the Lord, riches and glory and life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:5",
      "text": "Arms and swords are in the way of the perverse: but he that keepeth his own soul, departeth far from them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:6",
      "text": "It is a proverb: A young man according to his way, even when he is old, he will not depart from it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:7",
      "text": "The rich ruleth over the poor: and the borrower is servant to him that lendeth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:8",
      "text": "He that soweth iniquity, shall reap evils, and with the rod of his anger he shall be consumed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:9",
      "text": "He that is inclined to mercy, shall be blessed: for of his bread he hath given to the poor. He that maketh presents, shall purchase victory and honour: but he carrieth away the souls of the receivers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:10",
      "text": "Cast out the scoffer, and contention shall go out with him, and quarrels and reproaches shall cease.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:11",
      "text": "He that loveth cleanness of heart, for the grace of his lips shall have the king for his friend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:12",
      "text": "The eyes of the Lord preserve knowledge: and the words of the unjust are overthrown.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:13",
      "text": "The slothful man saith: There is a lion without, I shall be slain in the midst of the streets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:14",
      "text": "The mouth of a strange woman is a deep pit: he whom the Lord is angry with, shall fall into it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:15",
      "text": "Folly is bound up in the heart of a child, and the rod of correction shall drive it away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:16",
      "text": "He that oppresseth the poor, to increase his own riches, shall himself give to one that is richer, and shall be in need.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:17",
      "text": "Incline thy ear, and hear the words of the wise: and apply thy heart to my doctrine:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:18",
      "text": "Which shall be beautiful for thee, if thou keep it in thy bowels, and it shall flow in thy lips:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:19",
      "text": "That thy trust may be in the Lord, wherefore I have also shewn it to thee this day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:20",
      "text": "Behold I have described it to thee three manner of ways, in thoughts and knowledge:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:21",
      "text": "That I might shew thee the certainty, and the words of truth, to answer out of these to them that sent thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:22",
      "text": "Do no violence to the poor, because he is poor: and do not oppress the needy in the gate:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:23",
      "text": "Because the Lord will judge his cause: and will afflict them that have afflicted his soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:24",
      "text": "Be not a friend to an angry man, and do not walk with a furious man:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:25",
      "text": "Lest perhaps thou learn his ways, and take scandal to thy soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:26",
      "text": "Be not with them that fasten down their hands, and that offer themselves sureties for debts:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:27",
      "text": "For if thou have not wherewith to restore, what cause is there that he should take the covering from thy bed?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:28",
      "text": "Pass not beyond the ancient bounds which thy fathers have set.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.22.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:29",
      "text": "Hast thou seen a man swift in his work? he shall stand before kings, and shall not be before those that are obscure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
